<LEADPARA>  Merlin Olsen would have burst with pride at the formal sensibilities of San
Jose Mayor Susan Hammer's chief aide, Gary Robinson. Looking to spruce up the
council's sixth-floor reception room, Robinson queried other council offices
about whether they might like flowers. Sure, came the response. So every week,
the room now gets a new $28 floral arrangement, a cost of less than $1,500 per
year. A few of the council aides were a bit surprised when they saw that the
bill for the flowers was tacked on to the council's general tab. But no one is
griping publicly. "I don't mind," said Councilman David Pandori. "I don't
consider it a big deal." And Robinson? "We've gotten compliments but no
complaints," he said.; BEATING THE ODDS  </LEADPARA>
